Toss the oil and vinegar with all the beetroot and season well.Mix the dill with the crème fraîche and season.Place the flour in a large bowl and whisk in the beer, a little at a time, until smooth.Preheat a deep-fat fryer to 180C (CAUTION: hot oil can be dangerous. Do not leave unattended).Dust the mackerel with flour, shaking off the excess, dip into the batter and fry for 3–5 minutes, or until golden-brown. Drain on kitchen paper and season well.Divide the beetroots between two plates and top with the dill crème fraîche. Place the mackerel on top and garnish with rocket.